 Cut Rotted Fence Bottoms & Install Kickboard (~40 Linear Feet) Project Description: Hi, I am looking for a quote to repair a section of my wooden privacy fence (approx. 40 linear feet) in San Antonio. The Issue: The bottom 2-3 inches of the fence pickets have rotted due to ground contact and standing water. The rest of the fence is in stable condition. The Scope of Work needed: Cut & Trim: Snap a line and cut the bottom of the pickets straight across to remove the rotted portions (approx. 2-3 inches up). Install Kickboard: Supply and install a 2x6 pressure-treated "rot board" (kickboard) at the bottom to seal the gap and protect the pickets from future ground contact. Materials: Use galvanized or exterior-grade screws (no nails) for the new board. Site Conditions: There is some standing water/mud along the fence line that needs to be worked around (see photos). Easy access to the yard. Optional: Please list the rot repair as the main quote. If you also offer drainage solutions (grading or french drain) to fix the standing water shown in the photos, please list that as a separate line item or "optional add-on." Thank you!
